=== Installation

- Update package list and upgrade existing packages:
```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
```
- Install the broker (`mosquitto`) and CLI tools (`mosquitto_pub`, `mosquitto_sub`):
```bash
sudo apt install mosquitto mosquitto-clients -y
```
- Check the service status:
```bash
sudo systemctl status mosquitto
```
- You may need to enable and start the service manually:
```bash
sudo systemctl enable mosquitto
sudo systemctl start mosquitto
```

---

=== Configuration

- Main config file: `/etc/mosquitto/mosquitto.conf`
- Custom configs go in `/etc/mosquitto/conf.d/*.conf`
// - Minimal listener config placed in `/etc/mosquitto/conf.d/custom.conf`:
```config
listener 1883
allow_anonymous false
password_file /etc/mosquitto/passwd
```
- Restart after changes:
```
sudo systemctl restart mosquitto
```
- Check the broker status/logs:
```bash
sudo systemctl status mosquitto
sudo journalctl -u mosquitto -f
```

---

=== User Authentication

- Create the password file and first user:
```
sudo mosquitto_passwd -c /etc/mosquitto/passwd <username1>
```
- Add another user: _(no `-c`, or it overwrites the file)_
```
sudo mosquitto_passwd /etc/mosquitto/passwd <username2>
```
- Ensure `passwd` file has the proper owernship.
```bash
sudo chown mosquitto:mosquitto /etc/mosquitto/passwd
sudo chmod 600 /etc/mosquitto/passwd
```

---

=== Testing Pub/Sub

#info[It is recommended to install `tmux` for testing:
  ```bash
  sudo apt install tmux -y
  ```
]

- Subscribe _(terminal 1)_:
```
mosquitto_sub -h localhost -t test/topic -u <username> -P "<password>"
```
- Publish _(terminal 2)_:
```
mosquitto_pub -h localhost -t test/topic -m "hello" -u <username> -P "<password>"
```

